    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beds with an unsupported canopy, typically shorter than the bed; there are no posts on a lit d'ange, although sometimes the term is used incorrectly to refer to types of canopy beds with posts. For grander beds with a frame supporting the canopy, use "lits à la duchesse."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
